self.title: CDISC SEND Microscopic Findings Test Code Terminology

definition: Terminology for the test codes concerned with the non-clinical findings from a specimen that are visible by microscopic analysis.
name: SEND Microscopic Findings Test Code
preferredTerm: CDISC SEND Microscopic Findings Test Code Terminology

terms.definition: A qualitative microscopic examination of tissue sections to determine the presence of pathologic finding(s). This term is intended to be used for non-targeted examinations.
A qualitative microscopic examination of reproductive tissue sections to determine the phase of the reproductive cycle.
A qualitative microscopic examination of reproductive tissue sections to determine sexual maturity.
